Privacy Policy for Sohan Bot
Last updated: June 3, 2025

This Privacy Policy outlines how the Sohan Discord Bot (“we”, “our”, or “the bot”) collects, uses, and protects your data.

1. Information We Collect

Server IDs and User IDs

Command usage logs

Temporary data required for bot features to function

We do not collect sensitive personal information such as emails, passwords, IP addresses, or payment information.

2. How We Use the Data

To enable core bot functionality and features

To analyze performance and improve the bot

To prevent abuse, spam, or misuse

3. Data Sharing

We do not sell, rent, or trade your data with third parties.

Data may be shared only when required by law (e.g., legal subpoenas or court orders).

4. Data Retention

Data is stored only as long as necessary to support the bot’s operations.

Temporary data is discarded shortly after use.

5. Your Rights

You may request that we delete your stored data by contacting us via our support server.

You have the right to know what data we collect and how it is used.

6. Third-Party Services

Our bot operates within Discord and is subject to Discord’s Privacy Policy.

We are not responsible for how Discord or any third-party service handles your data.

7. Changes to This Policy

This Privacy Policy may be updated from time to time.

Changes will be posted on our website and take effect immediately upon posting.

8. Contact
If you have questions or concerns, please contact us through our Support Server: https://discord.gg/NrdCRXWr43
